---

# 🐳 Visitor App

A simple **Flask + Redis** application running in Docker.

---

## 📦 Prerequisites

* A Linux VM (EC2 or similar)
* Docker installed
* Git installed

---

## 🚀 Setup Instructions

### 1️⃣ Log into VM & Install Dependencies

```bash
sudo yum install docker -y
sudo yum install git -y
```

### 2️⃣ Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone <this-git-repo-link>
cd <repo-name>
```

### 3️⃣ Configure Docker on VM

```bash
sudo service docker start
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
```

> ⚠️ After adding the user to the `docker` group, **log out and log back in** for changes to take effect.

### 4️⃣ Build Docker Image

```bash
docker build -t visitor-app .
```

### 5️⃣ Create a Docker Network

```bash
docker network create visitor-net
```

### 6️⃣ Run Containers

Start Redis:

```bash
docker run -d --name redis --network visitor-net redis:alpine
```

Start Flask App:

```bash
docker run -d --name web-app --network visitor-net -p 5000:5000 visitor-app
```

### 7️⃣ Verify Running Containers

```bash
docker ps
```

---

## 🌍 Access the App

Open in your browser:

```
http://<EC2-PUBLIC-IP>:5000
```

